citations:
  citation-awoiaf-daenys-targaryen:
    source: source-awoiaf
    properties:
      locator: "Daenys Targaryen"
      accessed: "2026-03-15"
    notes: "Female, Valyrian culture. House Targaryen. Born before 126 BC in Valyria. Died after 101 BC on Dragonstone. Title: Lady of Dragonstone. Father: Aenar Targaryen. Spouse: Gaemon Targaryen (brother). Known as Daenys the Dreamer. Foresaw the Doom of Valyria in prophetic dreams, persuading her father to move the family to Dragonstone in 114 BC. Wrote Signs and Portents (now lost)."
